igration of Chinese laborers to the United States.         Teaching Against Anti-Asian Racism     Teaching Resources   This is a document listing teaching resources including scholarly work, news articles, grassroots resources, reports, and pedagogical strategies for teaching in the age of this pandemic. This is a document co-produced by Professors Anna Guevarra, Michael Jin, and Gayatri Reddy.  Download document here .     Work-in-Progress Syllabus   We are currently developing an open access syllabus on “Coronavirus and Anti-Asian Racism.”  Document will be available for download soon.             Career & Resources    Back to main content           Career Information    Alumni Spotlight     Ada Tong, Class of 2016    Naomi Leilani Salcedo, Class of 2016    Brandon Lee, Class of 2009      Asian American Studies Program Archive     Kamal Kishore Kapur Memorial Prize    ASAM Faculty – Led Study Abroad Program     Japan Study Abroad Program 2014    India Study Abroad Program 2013    India Study Abroad Program 2012      ASAM Community Engagement    Newsletters      Asian Studies Archive     Requirements for Minor    Courses    Upcoming Grants and Conferences    News & Events      Teaching Against Racism                   UIC Logo         College Of  Liberal Arts  And  Sciences         Contact   Global Asian Studies  601 S. Morgan St., 1051 UH Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 355-3448  Fax: (312) 996-9839  glas@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    LinkedIn    Twitter    Instagram            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 